---
import Layout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="John Miller - Author & Founder | Journaling Techniques">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="bg-[#fafafa] pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-0 px-0">
    
    <div class="relative">
      
      <div class="md:sticky md:top-25 z-20 bg-[#fafafa]/80 backdrop-blur-md pb-8">
        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:mb-8 pt-8 md:pt-0">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-10">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 md:w-40 md:h-40 rounded-[20px] bg-indigo-100 flex-shrink-0 overflow-hidden border-4 border-white shadow-xl">
               <img src="https://dev.journalingtechniques.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/3c49439f-d94c-4347-b78c-cb25f5d7f0d7.jpg" alt="John Miller" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-4">John Miller</h1>
              <p class="text-slate-600 font-bold text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
                10+ Years of Experience in Expressive Writing, Daily Journaling & Personal Development
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 mb-20 mt-12 md:mt-0 relative z-10">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
          <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-6 text-slate-500 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              John Miller has spent over a decade doing one thing most people only talk about — sitting down every single day and writing. Not for an audience or publication, but for the same reason he eventually built this website: because writing about your life is one of the most powerful things a person can do for their mind.
            </p>
            <p>
              What started as a single notebook on a quiet morning more than ten years ago became a practice, then a passion, and eventually a purpose.
            </p>
            
            <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 pt-6">His Journey</h2>
            <p>
              John came to journaling through a difficult period in his life when thinking alone was not enough. He needed somewhere to put his thoughts. Over time, the anxiety began to loosen, and patterns in his own behavior started showing up on the page, plain and undeniable.
            </p>
            <p>
              That curiosity led him to research Dr. James Pennebaker's studies, the neuroscience of handwriting, and every method from Shadow Work to Morning Pages. He is a genuine practitioner who wants to understand what actually works and why.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-4 space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-4">Experience</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-4">
                <li class="flex gap-3 text-xs font-bold text-slate-700"><span>📓</span> 10+ Years Daily Practice</li>
                <li class="flex gap-3 text-xs font-bold text-slate-700"><span>🔬</span> Expressive Writing Research</li>
                <li class="flex gap-3 text-xs font-bold text-slate-700"><span>✍️</span> 48+ Tested Techniques</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div> <section class="relative z-30 bg-slate-900 py-24 text-white text-center">
       <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
         <p class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-black italic mb-8 leading-tight">
            "Journaling is not about becoming a better writer. It is about becoming a more honest thinker."
         </p>
         <span class="text-indigo-400 text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">— John Miller</span>
       </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 bg-white relative z-30">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 mb-20">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-4">What He Writes About</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              John writes about <strong>Journaling Techniques</strong> (methods and science) and <strong>Daily Life Writing</strong> (the quieter, personal side of growth).
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              His writing is not motivational; it is the work of someone who has spent ten years paying attention to what genuinely helps people build a habit that lasts.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-indigo-50/50 p-8 rounded-3xl border border-indigo-100">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-slate-900 mb-4 text-center">Want to contribute?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm text-center mb-6">John personally reviews every pitch and submission.</p>
            <a href="mailto:hello@journalingtechniques.org" class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 text-indigo-600 font-bold hover:text-indigo-800 transition-colors">
              <span>📧</span> hello@journalingtechniques.org
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>